I remember when...<br>
<br>
- Magician pets didn't have spells (especially earth!)<br>
- Magicians had no pet heals.<br>
- Damage shields lasted for hours if cast on a pet.<br>
- My first sight of a Butcherblock sunset....awe inspiring.<br>
- D'Vinn to zone!<br>
- Spending a few quite hours fishing on the shores of Lake Rathe.<br>
- I spent 2 days camping a Dragoon Dirk.<br>
- There are 87 players in South Karana.<br>
- The most common shout in Greater Faydark was &quot;Has anybody seen my corpse?&quot;<br>
- Nobody understood what enchanters could do and they couldn't get groups.<br>
- The thrill of my first Giant &amp; Griffon revenge kills.<br>
- You could bind anywhere (ok you can still do this on blue servers but it's been years since I last played on one).<br>
- Taking almost a month to get out of level 30 and two months to get out of level 35.<br>
- Accidentally nuking another player or NPC while standing around outside the bank practicing spells...<br>
- Kedge Keep wasn't itemised.<br>
- You could meet new friends while hanging out waiting for the boat. I miss not having to use boats. <br>
