- Warriors before they got critical hits, and they didn't even know they &quot;needed&quot; them.<br>
- Not knowing you actually had to train a point in Taunt for it to go up.<br>
- Not knowing you could actually run to a zoneline to escape death.<br>
- Waiting for someone to come to town and sell some fine steel or ringmail.<br>
- That bastard Kobold in Innothule Swamp (dammit, what was his name?  Did it start with a J?)<br>
- Those bastard elves and humans running around Innothule swamp and killing the baby trolls.<br>
- Thinking that a Darkweed snake's poison can't be <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>that</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> bad.<br>
- Corpse runs at level 1<br>
- Stumbling into Nektulos Forest, at night, as a Human, and not even knowing what just killed you.<br>
- Trying to find Nektulos Forest again, at night, as a Human, to get your things back.<br>
- Terrorantula!!<br>
- Banking all your stuff and running to another city naked in case you got killed on the way.<br>
- Having a group member say &quot;wow!&quot; when your rusty 2-hander just hit something for 21 damage.<br>
- Seeing someone in full banded mail with a surname!<br>
- Naming Parties (as mentioned, when you /petitioned to get a surname).  Of course you had to actually <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>get</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to the party, which involved banking all your stuff and running naked.<br>
- Having to reply to a /tell by typing /tell &lt;character name&gt;<br>
- Not knowing all the stupid shorthand names for items<br>
- The first time you heard &quot;Ding!&quot; and cringed.  I still cringe.<br>
- Fattees, skinnees, and shortees!<br>
<br>
and finally....<br>
